*{{IPA|/ˈrɛkwiˌɛm/ ''or'' /ˈrɛkwi.əm/}}

===Noun===
'''requiem'''
# a [[mass]] to [[honor]] a dead person
#: ''[[Requiem]] aeternam dona eis, Domine, et lux perpetua luceat eis.'' - "Grant them eternal rest, O Lord, and may everlasting light shine upon them." (''Typical opening to such a mass'')
